                <article class="content">
                    <section class="intro">
                        <div class="tag-container">
                            <span class="tag">Core Concept</span>
                            <span class="tag">The Basics</span>
                            <span class="tag">No Cap</span>
                        </div>
                        <p class="lead">CURSED is an esoteric programming language designed to combine the simplicity and efficiency of Go with the contemporary linguistic flair of Generation Z slang. This overview gives you the whole vibe in one page.</p>
                    </section>

                    <section>
                        <h2>What Makes CURSED Different?</h2>
                        <p>CURSED isn't just another programming language - it's a whole mood. Here's what sets it apart:</p>
                        
                        <div class="feature-box">
                            <h3>Core Design Principles</h3>
                            <ul class="vibe-list">
                                <li><span class="emoji">ud83dudcac</span> <strong>Syntactic Familiarity with a Twist:</strong> Go-like grammar with Gen Z slang keywords</li>
                                <li><span class="emoji">ud83dudd04</span> <strong>Self-Hosting:</strong> Designed to compile itself through bootstrapping</li>
                                <li><span class="emoji">ud83eudd70</span> <strong>Pragmatic Absurdity:</strong> Esoteric by design yet fully functional</li>
                                <li><span class="emoji">ud83dudcbc</span> <strong>Compilation Efficiency:</strong> Produces efficient code without sacrificing readability</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </section>

                    <section class="code-example">
                        <h2>What It Looks Like</h2>
                        <p>CURSED code has that unique aesthetic while being totally readable:</p>
                        
                        <div class="code-block">
                            <div class="code-title">hello_world.csd</div>
                            <pre><code>vibe main

yeet "vibez"

slay main() {
    vibez.spill("It's giving hello world!")
}</code></pre>
                        </div>
                        
                        <p>Yes, those keywords are fr fr. Here's another example with more features:</p>
                        
                        <div class="code-block">
                            <div class="code-title">fibonacci.csd</div>
                            <pre><code>vibe math_vibez

yeet "vibez"

slay fibonacci(n normie) normie {
    lowkey n <= 1 {
        yolo n
    }
    yolo fibonacci(n-1) + fibonacci(n-2)
}

slay main() {
    bestie i := 0; i < 10; i++ {
        vibez.spillf("Fibonacci %d: %d\n", i, fibonacci(i))
    }
}</code></pre>
                        </div>
                    </section>

                    <section>
                        <h2>Language Characteristics</h2>
                        <p>CURSED brings all the main character energy with these features:</p>
                        
                        <div class="feature-box">
                            <ul class="vibe-list">
                                <li><span class="emoji">ud83dudd0d</span> <strong>Static Typing with Inference:</strong> Combine safety with convenience</li>
                                <li><span class="emoji">ud83duddd1ufe0f</span> <strong>Automatic Garbage Collection:</strong> No memory management stress</li>
                                <li><span class="emoji">u26a1</span> <strong>Built-in Concurrency:</strong> Goroutines and channels for parallelism</li>
                                <li><span class="emoji">ud83dudce6</span> <strong>Package System:</strong> Modular code organization</li>
                                <li><span class="emoji">ud83euddee</span> <strong>Expression-Based:</strong> Most constructs yield values</li>
                                <li><span class="emoji">ud83eudde9</span> <strong>Generics:</strong> Type-safe polymorphic code</li>
                                <li><span class="emoji">ud83dudd04</span> <strong>Self-Hosting Compiler:</strong> Built in CURSED itself</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </section>

                    <section>
                        <h2>Target Audience</h2>
                        <p>CURSED is designed for:</p>
                        
                        <div class="tips-grid">
                            <div class="tip-card">
                                <div class="tip-icon">ud83dudc7e</div>
                                <h3>Language Enthusiasts</h3>
                                <p>People who love exploring new programming language concepts and designs.</p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="tip-card">
                                <div class="tip-icon">ud83cudf93</div>
                                <h3>Compiler Students</h3>
                                <p>Those studying compiler design and implementation techniques.</p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="tip-card">
                                <div class="tip-icon">ud83dude0e</div>
                                <h3>Unique Experience Seekers</h3>
                                <p>Developers looking for a fresh, fun programming experience.</p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="tip-card">
                                <div class="tip-icon">ud83dudcac</div>
                                <h3>Language-Culture Explorers</h3>
                                <p>Those interested in how culture and language intersect with coding.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </section>

                    <section>
                        <h2>Implementation Strategy</h2>
                        <p>CURSED follows a bootstrap compiler approach:</p>
                        
                        <ol>
                            <li><strong>Stage 0:</strong> Initial compiler developed in Rust</li>
                            <li><strong>Stage 1:</strong> Self-compilation of a bootstrap compiler</li>
                            <li><strong>Stage 2:</strong> Development of a full CURSED compiler in CURSED</li>
                            <li><strong>Stage 3:</strong> Self-compilation of the full compiler</li>
                        </ol>
                        
                        <p>Each stage expands the language's feature set until it reaches its complete specification. For more details, check out the <a href="bootstrapping.html">bootstrapping page</a>.</p>
                    </section>

                    <section>
                        <h2>Packages and Modules</h2>
                        <p>CURSED uses a simple module system based on packages:</p>
                        
                        <div class="feature-box">
                            <ul class="vibe-list">
                                <li><span class="emoji">ud83dudce6</span> <strong>Package Declaration:</strong> Every source file belongs to a package, declared with <code>vibe PackageName;</code></li>
                                <li><span class="emoji">ud83dudcbc</span> <strong>Exports:</strong> Symbols starting with an uppercase letter are exported (public)</li>
                                <li><span class="emoji">ud83euddee</span> <strong>Imports:</strong> The <code>yeet</code> keyword imports other packages</li>
                                <li><span class="emoji">ud83dudd0d</span> <strong>Qualified Access:</strong> Imported symbols are accessed using the package name</li>
                                <li><span class="emoji">ud83cudfa8</span> <strong>Import Aliases:</strong> Optional aliases can be provided during import</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </section>

